steps.instruction:
### Prep
- Beat eggs

1. In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the sugars, flour, salt, and spices
2. In a large measuring cup, beat together the eggs, pumpkin, and cream or evaporated milk
3. Whisk into the dry ingredients
4. For best flavor, cover and refrigerate the filling overnight before baking
5. Lightly grease a 9" pie pan that's at least 1 1/2" deep
6. Roll the pie dough out to a 13" circle, and transfer to the pan
7. Crimp the edges above the rim; this will give you a little extra headroom to hold the filling when it expands in the oven
8. Refrigerate the crust while the oven preheats to 400F
9. When the oven is hot, place the pie pan on a baking sheet to catch any drips
10. Pour the filling into the unbaked pie shell
11. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, until the filling is set 2" in from the edge
12. Take out of oven when done
     - The center should still be wobbly
13. Let cool on a wire rack
    - The center will finish cooking through as the pie sits

#### Tips
- Mixing the filling a day in advance (refrigerate until using) will improve the flavor of this pie by giving the spices' flavors a chance to blend
- For a Masala Pumpkin Pie, make these changes to the spice mixture for the filling: decrease cinnamon to 1/2 teaspoon, increase ground cloves to 1/4 teaspoon and black pepper to 1/2 teaspoon. Add 1/2 teaspoon each ground coriander and turmeric, and 1/4 teaspoon each ground cardamom and cumin
- Try replacing 1/4 cup of the all-purpose flour in your pie crust recipe with 1/4-cup cornmeal. The texture of the cornmeal is a nice counterpoint to the smooth pumpkin filling
- Substitute a generous 2 1/2 teaspoons Pumpkin Pie Spice for the spices listed, if desired
-This recipe makes enough filling to generously fill a 9" pan that's at least 1 1/2" deep. If your pan isn't quite that big, you can bake any leftover filling in custard cups; it will take 25 to 30 minutes to cook
